TITLE: "Senate ethics panel admonishes Lindsey Graham over campaign solicitations"
DESCRIPTION: The ethics panel found that the South Carolina Republican improperly solicited contributions from inside a federal building.

TITLE: "Kids to require parental consent to access social media apps under new Utah law"
DESCRIPTION: Utah becomes the first state to enact a law attempting to limit teens' access to social media sites.

TITLE: "House intel panel chairman says ban or sale of TikTok appears inevitable"
DESCRIPTION: House Intelligence Committee Chairman Mike Turner told CBS News a divestiture, ban or something to that effect will need to happen.

TITLE: "Proud Boys trial disrupted after defense says its witness was paid FBI informant"
DESCRIPTION: The judge overseeing the Proud Boys trial says he will not delay trial because of the revelation.

TITLE: "State Department facing "unprecedented demand" for passports, Blinken says"
DESCRIPTION: A record number of passports — 22 million — were issued in 2022. The State Department is "on track to break" that record in 2023.

TITLE: "House GOP fails to override Biden veto of ESG investing ban"
DESCRIPTION: The standoff was a first test of the strength of the new Republican majority in the House as it confronts the Democratic president in the White House.

TITLE: "Mark Ridley-Thomas Corruption Trial Almost In The Hands Of The Jury"
DESCRIPTION: The prosecution and defense made their closing arguments Thursday. The prosecution will conclude its rebuttal argument Friday and then the case will go to the jury.

TITLE: "Mother of Ashli Babbitt meets with House Speaker Kevin McCarthy"
DESCRIPTION: She met Thursday with House Speaker Kevin McCarthy, in his Capitol office suite — steps away from where her daughter was shot.

TITLE: "Manhattan grand jury investigating Trump unlikely to decide on any possible charges this week, sources say"
DESCRIPTION: Any vote on a possible indictment against Trump would be pushed into next week.
